messages.name: Does more updates than Niantic
messages.text: Processing can be intense and I can queue the tasks. Amazon s3 is great for housing static stuff it‚Äôs cheap. I don‚Äôt know how much you know about requests, but when you go to a website, you request that page, and then make a request for each style sheet, JavaScript page, and each and every image and video. So I limit the requests to my server that does the web work to only web page info, and let amazon handle the static stuff.

messages.name: Does more updates than Niantic
messages.text: I am rare in that I do both front end development, back end development, and the design.

messages.name: Does more updates than Niantic

messages.name: Does more updates than Niantic
messages.text: I have servers set up to handle media, so the pokestop images, gym images, the gallery images and videos, I process on that server. Create the different sizes, encode videos for all browsers and such. Then they are moved to an Amazon server. I have servers that process messaging. Email, phone text, Facebook, Twitter, and GroupMe happen there. I have the webserver that handles the website and database. It‚Äôs a lot to build at once. I built several sites like http://www.aotourism.com and http://www.campflorida.com that use this system setup. I have been building sites for 18 years.
